      <div class="group-right">
      <h2><a href="/ideas/2017/chaniotis-world-of-emotions">A World of Emotions: The Making of an Exhibition</a></h2>
<p class="field-ias-multiple-authors">
      <span class="field-ias-mutiple-authors__authors">
      By <a href="/scholars/chaniotis">Angelos Chaniotis</a>    </span>
  </p>

  <div class="field-grid-item-teaser">
    What are the means through which ancient artists represented the emotions of gods, mythical heroes, and “real” people? How were images and texts exploited to arouse emotions in an ancient (and modern) audience?  </div>
    </div>
  
  <div class="group-footer">
      </div>

</div>

