<article class="block block-views block-featured-scolars views-featured-scholars-block block--even block--last">
  <div class="block__inner views-featured-scholars-block__inner" >

            
    <div class="block__content views-featured-scholars-block__content">
      <div class="view view-featured-scholars view-id-featured_scholars view-display-id-block view-flex-grid grid-col-2 underlined-links animated img-opacity view-dom-id-bba358a6647ba39667dd790119a1db92">
            <div class="view-header">
      <p><a href="/scholars" class="f-sans">Faculty and Members</a></p>    </div>
  
  
  
      <div class="view-content">
        <div class="views-row views-row-1 views-row-odd views-row-first">
    <div  about="/ann-mcgrath-sss" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document" class="ds-1col node node-featured-scholar node--odd node--featured-scholar node--featured-scholar--full node--odd node--featured-scholar node--featured-scholar--full node-featured-scholar--image-left node-featured-scholar--image-left view-mode-full clearfix">

  
  
  <div class="field-body">
    <p>The School’s founders had not anticipated trouble, for surely no white woman would marry an “Indian,” let alone leave the United States to emigrate to the imperiled Cherokee Nation.</p>
<h4><em><a href="/scholars/ann-mcgrath">Ann McGrath</a> in </em><em><a href="/ideas/2016/mcgrath-history">Going Against History?</a></em></h4>  </div>
  <div class="field-ias-ft-scholar-img round-img">
    <img class="circular position--left field-ias-ft-scholar-img__image" typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://www.ias.edu/sites/default/files/styles/square_small/public/featured-scholars/mcgrath.png?itok=IowLIb2a" width="310" height="310" />  </div>
</div>

  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-2 views-row-even">
    <div  about="/hassan-ansari-shs" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document" class="ds-1col node node-featured-scholar node--even node--featured-scholar node--featured-scholar--full node--even node--featured-scholar node--featured-scholar--full node-featured-scholar--image-left node-featured-scholar--image-left view-mode-full clearfix">

  
  
  <div class="field-body">
    <p>The fact that she is a woman does not prevent the Shiite from considering her . . . as the teacher and divine guide.</p>
<p><em><a href="/scholars/hassan-farhang-ansari">Member Hassan Ansari</a> in <a href="/ideas/2016/ansari-shiite-women">The Shiite Interpretation of the Status of Women</a></em></p>  </div>
  <div class="field-ias-ft-scholar-img round-img">
    <img class="circular position--left field-ias-ft-scholar-img__image" typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://www.ias.edu/sites/default/files/styles/square_small/public/featured-scholars/ANSARIPatriciaCrone-Memorial_20151025_AK_241.png?itok=QFbH8loa" width="310" height="310" />  </div>
</div>

  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-3 views-row-odd">
    <div  about="/olga-holtz-my-random-walks-p%C3%B3lya-and-szeg%C5%91-math" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document" class="ds-1col node node-featured-scholar node--odd node--featured-scholar node--featured-scholar--full node--odd node--featured-scholar node--featured-scholar--full node-featured-scholar--image-right node-featured-scholar--image-right view-mode-full clearfix">

  
  
  <div class="field-body">
    <p>I read the introduction to <em>Mathematics and Plausible Reasoning</em> and its Chapter I standing up next to the bookshelf. It read like a novel. </p>
<h4><em><a href="/scholars/olga-holtz">Olga Holtz</a> in <a href="/ideas/2014/holtz-random">My Random Walks with Pólya and Szegő</a></em></h4>  </div>
  <div class="field-ias-ft-scholar-img round-img">
    <img class="circular position--right field-ias-ft-scholar-img__image" typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://www.ias.edu/sites/default/files/styles/square_small/public/featured-scholars/WaM_Colloquia_Olga-Holtz_20141414_DKomoda-0430%20copy.jpg?itok=qh8fLT7t" width="310" height="310" />  </div>
</div>

  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-4 views-row-even views-row-last">
    <div  about="/freeman-dyson-toast-einstein-sns" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document" class="ds-1col node node-featured-scholar node--even node--featured-scholar node--featured-scholar--full node--even node--featured-scholar node--featured-scholar--full node-featured-scholar--image-right node-featured-scholar--image-right view-mode-full clearfix">

  
  
  <div class="field-body">
    <p>General Relativity is half of the picture, and to my taste the more beautiful half.</p>
<h4><em><a href="/scholars/dyson">Freeman Dyson</a> in <a href="/ideas/2015/dyson-einstein">A Toast to Einstein</a></em></h4>  </div>
  <div class="field-ias-ft-scholar-img round-img">
    <img class="circular position--right field-ias-ft-scholar-img__image" typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://www.ias.edu/sites/default/files/styles/square_small/public/featured-scholars/Freeman_GR_Dinner_20151105_DKomoda-2653.jpg?itok=_ivoQH-t" width="310" height="310" />  </div>
</div>

  </div>
